<HEADLINE>
<P>
CIVIC VOLUNTEER EVELYN BAUMAN DIES AT AGE 75 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Evelyn Werther Bauman, a 45-year resident of the city and a longtime civic 
volunteer, died Sunday. She was 75. 
</P>
<P>
 Born in Dover, Ohio, Bauman was graduated from Mt.Union College in Alliance, 
Ohio, and worked as a medical laboratory technician. She was married to her 
college sweetheart, Don Bauman, for 50 years. 
</P>
<P>
 After moving to Fullerton in 1949, Evelyn Bauman became active in various 
community and cultural activities. She was named Fullerton Woman of the Year in 
1966, received the north Orange County YMCA silver medallion for community 
service, and, in 1993, was named volunteer of the year by Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Services will be Sunday at 5 p.m. at the Fullerton First United Methodist 
Church, with a reception following at 6:30 p.m. at the Titan Pavilion, Cal 
State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Instead of flowers, donations can be made to Habitat for Humanity, P.O. Box 
7086, Orange, CA. 92613; Nature Conservancy of California, 785 Market St., 3rd 
floor, San Francisco, CA. 94103; or the Evelyn Bauman Memorial for President's 
Associates Scholarship, Cal State University President's Office, 800 N. State 
College Blvd., Fullerton, CA. 92634. 
</P>
</TEXT>
