<P>
 VALLEY IRISH: A lot of eyes must be smiling in Burbank today. It's St. Paddy's 
Day, of course, and Burbank carries the largest contingent -- 3.6% -- of Valley 
folks with heavy Irish ancestry (above). . . . In all, according to the 1990 U. 
S. Census, 49,124 residents (2.6%) identified Irish as their main lineage. 
</P>
<P>
 SHUTTLE CHECK: Certainly, if you're going to fly into space, it's probably a 
good idea to check out your vehicle ahead of time. Which is exactly what 
happened Wednesday when the six-member crew that will fly on the modified 
Atlantis shuttle visited Palmdale. . . . The timing was perfect. NASA said 
Tuesday that major shuttle adjustments will continue to be done by Rockwell 
International in Palmdale. (B18) 
</P>
<P>
 VERSATILE TEEN: Sure, maybe he's no Bo Jackson or Deion Sanders, but 
Harvard-Westlake High senior Matt Sebree is a pretty impressive player in two 
sports -- football and volleyball. . . . Already, Notre Dame, Penn State and 
USC have shown interest in his kicking skills while the top volleyball schools 
want him too. (C12) 
</P>
<P>
 EARLY AMBITION: Speaking of talented teens, check out UCLA freshman Josh Arce, 
18. Arce, a Democrat, hopes this fall to dethrone Republican Paula Boland in 
the 38th Assembly District, covering the northwestern Valley. . . . So what if 
his campaign budget is only $150? So what if his own grandmother, a staunch 
Republican, wouldn't lend him money? "You can't win the game if you don't step 
out on the field," he said. (B5) 
</P>
<P>
 LOCAL HEROES: March Madness gets under way this week, and you can bet the 
Valley will have a say in the outcome of the college basketball tournaments. . 
. . For the men, the Valley alumni include UCLA's Marquis Burns, New Mexico 
State's D. J. Jackson and Pepperdine's Dana Jones. The women come from Hart 
High in Newhall -- Oregon State's Anjanette Dionne and Oregon's Sara Wilson. 
Where the Irish Are 
</P>
<P>
 Only 2.6% of Valley residents claim Irish as their main ancestry. Communities 
with the largest percentage of Irish residents: Burbank: 3.6% Sherman 
Oaks-Studio City*: 3.4% Sunland-Tujunga: 3.0% Chatsworth-Porter Ranch: 2.8% 
Reseda-West Van Nuys: 2.8% * Includes Toluca Lake 
</P>
<P>
 Source: U.S. Census Michael Arkush 
