<P>
2 MEN SOUGHT IN EL RIO SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies were searching for two men who waited for an El Rio man to 
return home, then fired several shots at him, striking him in the shoulder, 
officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The incident occurred between 9:30 and 10 p.m. Tuesday at the home of Raul 
Gomez in the 2500 block of Wright Road. Gomez was treated for a gunshot wound 
at St. John's Regional Medical Center in Oxnard and released. 
</P>
<P>
 Gomez told deputies that the two men had arrived at his house Tuesday evening 
and persuaded his wife, Irma, to let them wait inside. They did not harm the 
wife, Ventura County Sheriff's Sgt. Kelly Fadler said. 
</P>
<P>
 Raul Gomez told deputies that he did not know the men. 
</P>
