<P>
VOLUNTEERS NEEDED TO PREPARE SOCCER FIELD AT OXNARD COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Volunteers are needed Saturday to lay sod for a second soccer field at Oxnard 
College. 
</P>
<P>
 The field will be used this summer by international teams training for the 
World Cup championships, to be held for the first time in the United 
States.Oxnard College is an official World Cup training site, but because it 
did not have regulation-size soccer fields, the college has had to build two 
this month. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers, many of them college staff members and students, laid sod for the 
first field March 5. The volunteers worked so quickly that they spread about 
100,000 square feet of sod in less than seven hours, college officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The effort will start Saturday at 6:30 a.m. For information, call the 
college's public information office at 986-5809. 
</P>
