<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDUCATION; P.V. SCHOOLS: SUPERINTENDENT QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Supt. Michael W. Caston of Palos Verdes school district will soon leave the 
area that gave him his first teaching position in 1971. 
</P>
<P>
 Caston will leave his post April 6 and step in as superintendent of the Santa 
Barbara School District on April 7. 
</P>
<P>
 Caston said his resignation had probably surprised colleagues. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a great opportunity to take on a bigger district and it's a beautiful 
area . . . (but) it's been a positive time here and it's with mixed emotions 
that I'm leaving," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Caston grew up in Torrance and later attended El Camino College. He started 
his teaching career at the peninsula's Miraleste High School and then served as 
assistant principal and principal in the Capistrano School District in Orange 
County. 
</P>
<P>
 From 1980 to 1990, he held both assistant superintendent and superintendent 
positions in the Covina School District before his appointment to Palos Verdes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
