<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDUCATION; HARBOR MAGNET: ECOLOGY QUIZ VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A team of fifth- and sixth-grade students from the Harbor Math/Science Magnet 
Center in San Pedro won first place in an environment quiz at the Arboretum on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The students were competing against 29 other public and private schools in Los 
Angeles County as part of the Environmental Education Fair, said Lesley Arnold, 
the school's Parent Teacher Assn. president. The school is in the Los Angeles 
Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 The Nature Bowl quiz tested knowledge of rain forests, forces of energy and 
the changing nature of Earth, Arnold said. SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</TEXT>
