<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDUCATION; ARTS SCHOOL: AUDITIONS SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA RICHARDSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Auditions are being scheduled for students in grades 9 to 11 who want to 
enroll this fall in the Los Angeles County High School for the Arts. 
</P>
<P>
 Visual arts portfolio screenings and performance auditions in dance, theater, 
vocal and instrumental music will be held at 9 a.m. at Cal State Los Angeles on 
April 17. 
</P>
<P>
 Arts High School, operated by the Los Angeles County Office of Education, is a 
tuition-free, comprehensive public school. It offers instruction in dance, 
theater, music and visual arts, taught by working professionals. Students also 
take a full range of academic courses and may participate in the school's 
college-credit program. 
</P>
<P>
 To receive an application and set an audition appointment, students may call 
(213) 343-ARTS. The application deadline is March 25. 
</P>
<P>
 Spanish-speaking parents and students may obtain more information by calling 
Ben Fonseca at (213) 343-2565. LISA RICHARDSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
