<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HAWTHORNE; CITY ATTORNEY FIRED, WILL GET 6 MONTHS PAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT SANDELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Atty. Michael Adamson has been fired by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 After a public hearing followed by a closed-door meeting Monday night, the 
council voted 4 to 1 to dismiss Adamson effective March 25.Councilman Steven 
Andersen cast the dissenting vote, maintaining that Adamson had performed well 
for the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Assistant City Atty. Glen Shishido will continue as acting city attorney until 
a permanent replacement is found. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members remained tight-lipped at Monday's meeting about precisely why 
they fired Adamson, a 17-year veteran of the city attorney's office, saying the 
action was a personnel matter.  
</P>
<P>
 However, Councilwoman Ginny M. Lambert said last month that the council's plan 
to fire Adamson was linked to allegations by some council members that he had 
acted improperly to restructure his employment contract. The contract allowed 
Adamson to receive cash for a percentage of unused sick leave and vacation 
time. 
</P>
<P>
 In a public hearing Monday night, Adamson disputed those allegations and said 
he is the target of a political vendetta by the council. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of a termination clause in his contract, Adamson will continue to 
receive his monthly salary of almost $9,000 for six months. SCOTT SANDELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
