<P>
South Bay; Part J; Page 15 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
157 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
IMMIGRATION DISCUSSION AT TORRANCE LIBRARY TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Representatives from government and immigration groups will speak at a panel 
discussion on immigration tonight at the Torrance Public Library. 
</P>
<P>
 Prof. David M. Heer, associate director of the Population Research Laboratory 
at USC, will moderate the discussion, titled "Immigration: The Causes, 
Perceptions, Problems, Impact and Alternative Approaches."It is sponsored by 
the Beach Cities, Palos Verdes Peninsula and Torrance chapters of the League of 
Women Voters. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants in the discussion include Ira Mehlman of the Federation for 
American Immigration Reform, Miguel Santana from Proponents for Responsible 
Immigration Debate and Education, Mark Tajima from the County Administrator's 
Office and Yoshi Matsushima of Coastal Asian Pacific Mental Health Services. 
</P>
<P>
 A lasagna dinner will be held from 6 to 7 p.m.; cost is $7. The free panel 
discussion begins at 7 p.m. The library is at 3301 Torrance Blvd. Phone: (310) 
618-5959. 
</P>
</TEXT>
