<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; PIPPEN STARS DESPITE BAD NIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scottie Pippen scored only 17 points on five-for-13 shooting, had a game-high 
six turnovers and was called for a technical foul with 3:07 left with the 
Chicago Bulls trailing the Boston Celtics by a point Wednesday night at Boston. 
</P>
<P>
 But Pippen hit a three-pointer with 51 seconds left to break a 98-98 tie and 
give the Bulls a 101-100 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Pippen's winning shot was the only three-pointer of the game. Boston's Dee 
Brown missed a three-pointer with 2.4 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 In other games: 
</P>
<P>
 Alonzo Mourning scored 20 points and had three blocked shots as the Charlotte 
Hornets limited Atlanta to 35% shooting in a 92-79 victory at Charlotte. . . . 
The Dallas Mavericks came close to stopping their current losing streak at 
eight, but Orlando's Donald Royal hit a fallaway jumper at the buzzer to give 
the Magic a 100-98 victory at Orlando. Shaquille O'Neal led Orlando with 34 
points and 21 rebounds. He made 12 of 12 free throws. . . . Reggie Miller 
scored 34 points as the Indiana Pacers defeated the Phoenix Suns, 109-98, at 
Indianapolis. . . . Dale Ellis and David Robinson scored 27 points apiece and 
Ellis came within two of becoming the first NBA player with 1,000 three-point 
goals as the San Antonio Spurs beat Portland, 110-102, at San Antonio. . . . 
Mitch Richmond scored 25 points and Olden Polynice had 16 points and 12 
rebounds in a 132-111 victory over New Jersey at Sacramento. The Kings scored 
46 points in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
