<HEADLINE>
<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; GOULET TAKES SCARY FALL AT MONTREAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michel Goulet of the Chicago Blackhawks regained full movement of his limbs 
after crashing into the boards during a a 5-3 loss to the Montreal Canadiens on 
Wednesday night at Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
 Goulet, 33, broke down the left side and partially fanned on a shot before he 
lost his footing and fell into the end boards 6:01 into the game.He had not 
been touched by an opposing player. 
</P>
<P>
 He was carried from the Forum ice on a stretcher and taken to a hospital with 
a concussion. 
</P>
<P>
 Initially, a Canadien team doctor said Goulet was unable to speak and opened 
his eyes only after he had been carried off the ice. 
</P>
<P>
 Later, a Canadien spokesman said Goulet was moving his limbs. He kept 
overnight for observation. OTHER GAMES 
</P>
<P>
 John Vanbiesbrouck made 34 saves in the Florida Panthers' 2-1 victory over the 
Calgary Flames at Miami. . . . Pavel Bure of the Vancouver Canucks scored his 
46th goal during a 4-1 victory over the Toronto Maple Leafs at Toronto. . . . 
Mike Richter made 27 saves in the New York Rangers' 4-0 victory over the 
Hartford Whalers at New York. . . . Tim Cheveldae stopped 41 shots during the 
Winnipeg Jets' 4-0 victory over the St. Louis Blues at Winnipeg. . . . The 
Tampa Bay Lightning and Edmonton Oilers tied, 4-4, at St. Petersburg, Fla. 
</P>
</TEXT>
