<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST AREA; CONSPIRACY TRIAL TO START FOR FATHER, SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former cable-TV host and his father will go to trial today in Norwalk 
Superior Court on charges they hired a hit man last year to kill a 14-year-old 
Pico Rivera girl whom the son was accused of raping. 
</P>
<P>
 Tito David Valdez Jr., 23, and his father, Tito David Valdez Sr., 56, both of 
Downey, are charged with conspiracy and solicitation to murder the girl.Tito 
Valdez Jr. was sentenced earlier this month to 14 years in prison after being 
convicted of rape and lewd conduct. 
</P>
<P>
 He and his father are accused of hiring a contract killer in early December to 
stop the girl from testifying. They were arrested several hours later and no 
murder attempt was made. Both defendants are in jail. 
</P>
<P>
 Tito Valdez Jr. hosted the "Hollywood Haze" program about the 
underground-party scene in the Southland. The show was aired last fall on 
Continental Cablevision, which serves several Southeast cities. 
</P>
