<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: BELL; LIBRARY EXTENDS HOURS TO 3 DAYS PER WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Bell Community Library will now be open Tuesdays, thanks to a deal between 
the city and county. 
</P>
<P>
 The library has been open just two days a week since state budget cuts forced 
the county government to cut library and other services last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The library in Bell is owned by the city but staffed by the county. Under the 
new agreement, the city will accept an extra day of county library services 
each week in exchange for rent, said City Administrator Robert A. Rizzo. 
</P>
<P>
 The county was paying $2,046 a month in rent and recently calculated the cost 
of operations at about $700 a day, Rizzo said. 
</P>
<P>
 Through June 21, the library hours are 1 to 8 p.m. Monday and Tuesday and 11 
a.m. to 6 p.m. Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
