<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; 
EX-PROBATION OFFICER PLEADS GUILTY TO CHILD PORN CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former Los Angeles County probation officer has pleaded guilty to federal 
child pornography charges, federal prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
 In pleading guilty to six counts of producing child pornography, Glenn Alan 
Nelson, 46, admitted he traveled to Thailand in 1991 to engage in sexually 
explicit conduct with boys under 18, Assistant U.S. Atty.Patricia Donahue said 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Nelson hired four boys in Bangkok and Pattaya, Thailand, to perform sexual 
acts. He is scheduled to be sentenced May 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies searched Nelson's home June 2, 1992, and found photographs 
of Nelson with the boys, and other child pornography. At the time, Nelson was 
working at Camp Scudder, a juvenile probation camp in Saugus. 
</P>
<P>
 Nelson fled before he could be charged. He was arrested last month in Joplin, 
Mo., on a warrant issued on a 29-count federal indictment for child 
pornography. 
</P>
</TEXT>
