<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: CERRITOS; ABC UNIFIED 
COULD FACE INSOLVENCY, REPORT SHOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The ABC Unified School District could become insolvent within three years 
unless the school board approves a multimillion-dollar budget-cutting plan, 
officials reported this week. 
</P>
<P>
 The gloomy outlook is contained in a three-year financial projection prepared 
for the county education office by top administrators of the Cerritos-area 
school system. 
</P>
<P>
 The administration submitted the report, as required by state law, in apparent 
defiance of the school board majority. The board argued that the district 
should report that it is in good financial shape. 
</P>
<P>
 Top administrators disagreed, however, and said the district's financial 
problems have been exacerbated by a tentative contract agreement with teachers 
that is will go before the board later this month. The contract restores 
smaller class sizes and pay that teachers lost under terms of an earlier 
contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
