</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fumes from a chemical apparently ingested by a child made some emergency room 
workers lightheaded at County-USC Medical Center on Wednesday night and 
prompted a response from a hazardous materials team. 
</P>
<P>
 "Initial reports are that it appears that the child has ingested some type of 
chemical, and the chemical was brought into the emergency room with the child," 
said Jim Wells, a Los Angeles Fire Department spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 The child was taken to the pediatric emergency room of the Women's Hospital at 
the medical center, Wells said.  
</P>
