<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 'COLD' O.C. HOT LINE MAY BE DISCONTINUED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A citizen hot line created to field suggestions about how Orange County 
government could be more efficient has run cold less than a year in 
operation.Since June, only 50 calls have been recorded, prompting Supervisor 
Thomas F. Riley to ask that the service be discontinued. 
</P>
<P>
 "I do not feel it appropriate to continue a service which is not being 
utilized by the residents of Orange County," Riley said in a memo to County 
Administrative Officer Ernie Schneider. "Therefore, I request the cancellation 
of the . . . line immediately." 
</P>
<P>
 Riley said that most of the calls were received in the first month of 
operation. KEVIN JOHNSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
