<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; FRESNO; EFFORT TO RECALL COUNCILMAN FAILS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An effort to force a recall election against Fresno Councilman Robert Smith 
has failed by 23 signatures.County elections official Cathy Cisneros said the 
recall petition contained 3,957 valid signatures but needed 3,980. She said 
more than 1,000 signatures were ruled invalid. The recall effort was triggered 
by Smith's opposition to renaming a street after the late farm labor leader 
Cesar Chavez after first supporting the change. 
</P>
