<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOPICS / POLICE BLOTTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AZUSA: A man wielding a sawed-off shotgun stole an undetermined amount of cash 
from the Ranch Market at 150 W. 9th St. about 9 p.m. Sunday. The man stormed 
into the market waving the gun, ordered customers to the floor and ransacked 
the register, witnesses said. He fled in a blue Chevy pickup truck that was 
waiting for him in the parking lot. No arrests were made and no injuries were 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
 ARCADIA: Four robbers armed with handguns and an Uzi entered a jewelry store 
at 921 S. Baldwin Ave. at 5:10 p.m. last Thursday, bound four employees with 
tape, and escaped with more than $200,000 in jewelry and cash, police said. 
None of the employees were injured and no arrests have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 CLAREMONT: A partial human skeleton was unearthed by a transient in a field 
near the city's border with Upland, police reported. The transient, who lives 
in the field north of Baseline Road and east of Padua Avenue, discovered a 
human pelvis, a spinal column that appeared to have been sawed off near the 
head and a number of other bones about 10:15 a.m. last Thursday. The Los 
Angeles County coroner is investigating.  
</P>
<P>
 PASADENA: A Long Beach exterminator survived multiple stab wounds during a 
carjacking early Thursday by pushing away from his attackers and running down a 
jogging track along the Arroyo Seco, police said. Matt Kohlwey, 22, left 
Islands Restaurant at 3533 E. Foothill Blvd. about 3 a.m. and was about to 
drive away when he was jumped by a group of men who forced him into the back of 
his pickup truck and drove to an area under the Colorado Street Bridge, police 
said. The men pulled Kohlwey out of the truck and stabbed him several times, 
puncturing at least one of his lungs, but he managed to run to a trail and 
escape. Kohlwey's truck was recovered intact about four hours later in 
northwest Pasadena, police said. He was listed in fair condition at Huntington 
Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: A 15-year-old was slain Tuesday night in a shooting at Cantera Street 
and Edgehill Drive, police said. Carlos Guzman was transported to Pomona Valley 
Hospital Medical Center after officers arrived at 9:20 p.m. Guzman died at the 
hospital shortly after arrival, police said. Witnesses told police they saw 
three or four men running from the scene to a waiting vehicle shortly after the 
shots were fired. No arrests have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 SOUTH PASADENA: A 19-year-old Arcadia man was the victim of a carjacking 
Tuesday night as he stood next to his 1985 Jeep Cherokee parked near Fair Oaks 
and Monterey avenues, police said. He said two men had approached him about 
9:30 p.m. and held a knife to his throat until he gave them the keys to his 
vehicle. No injuries were reported and no arrests have been made. 
</P>
