<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gary Anglin, the Ventura College baseball coach the past 17 years, will resign 
at the end of the season, Athletic Director Jerry Dunlap said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Anglin, 42, will continue to teach physical education at the school and will 
be an assistant on the football team next season. 
</P>
<P>
 He was the Western State Conference baseball coach of the year in 1989 and 
1992, when the Pirates went to the Southern California regional. 
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade High has scheduled an alumni baseball game April 2, and all former 
Chaminade players are eligible. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-252-6233. 
