<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Appoint Technologies Inc.: The Anaheim electronic-components manufacturer 
reported a profit of $1.3 million, or 9 cents a share, for its first fiscal 
quarter, which included a one-time gain of $1.7 million from discontinued 
operations.For the like period a year ago, a profit of $7,626, or less than 1 
cent a share, was recorded. Sales for the quarter ended Jan. 31 rose from 
$151,515 to $689,269. The 1994 figures included revenue of $475,140 and an 
operating loss of about $281,000 from an acquisition in November, 1993. 
</P>
