AURORA PLANS ACQUISITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aurora Electronics Inc. plans to acquire substantially all of the assets of 
Century Computer Marketing, a privately held firm in Marina del Rey, for about 
$33 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The price is composed of about $29 million cash and $4 million in Aurora 
common stock, plus the assumption of certain liabilities. The deal is subject 
to completion of the financing arrangements. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine-based Aurora, with 375 employees, reported profit of $3.1 million on 
revenue of $79 million for its fiscal year ended in September, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Century, which like Aurora distributes materials to and provides support for 
the computer industry, has 198 employees in its six facilities. The 10-year-old 
company had revenue of $40 million last year. 
