<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAMARILLO'S CORNELIUS WILL GIVE UP COACHING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Camarillo High volleyball Coach Bob Cornelius, who has coached the Scorpions 
girls' team for the last 13 years and the boys' team for the past seven years, 
said that he will quit coaching after this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Cornelius, 52, started the boys' program at Calabasas in 1988 and helped form 
the Frontier League for boys' volleyball the same year. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's been fun, but I've decided there are other things to do in my life," he 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031794-0349 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 023759 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 17, 1994, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
