<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; MISSING EL CENTRO WOMAN IS FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 70-year-old El Centro woman missing since Saturday was found Wednesday 
afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Eloisa Bermudiez Garrido, who walked away from her daughter's parked car near 
the Glendale Galleria, apparently wandered to a home near the mall, where she 
stayed until Wednesday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 The family called police at about 5 p.m. Wednesday, saying they could not 
determine who the woman was or where she was from. 
</P>
<P>
 "I just wish they would have called us earlier," Glendale police spokesman 
Lief Nicolaisen said.  
</P>
<P>
 Garrido, who suffers from diabetes and a heart condition, had wandered away 
from the parked car while her daughter, Mimi Garrido of Van Nuys, was shopping 
in the mall. She has been living with her daughter recently because of a series 
of doctors appointments, including cataract surgery last month. 
</P>
<P>
 Garrido was described by her daughter as a very outgoing person who would sit 
and talk with strangers for hours about her family. ED BOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
