<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SYLMAR; MISSION COLLEGE TO MARK 19TH BIRTHDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Irish music and food might lead revelers to think that the celebration at 
Mission College today is in honor of St. Patrick's Day. But actually, it's a 
party for the school's 19th birthday -- a month late. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our real birthday is in February, but we got off track with the earthquake," 
said Shari Borchetta, assistant to college President Jack Fujimoto. 
</P>
<P>
 The celebration program will take place at noon in the campus center on 
Eldridge Avenue in Sylmar and will introduce the college's interim vice 
president of academic affairs, Paul McKenna. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're tying it into St. Patrick's Day," said Neil Farren, dean of college 
advancement. "We're serving corned beef and (green) cabbage, potatoes, and 
we'll have Irish music." 
</P>
<P>
 McKenna is replacing Victoria Richart, who accepted a position as senior 
director of instructional and student services for the Los Angeles Community 
College District. 
</P>
<P>
 A Glendale resident, McKenna was director of instructional programs before 
joining the administration. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
